VFans of the cinema of Walter Salles (Central Station) will have had a cinematic initiation into the reality of Brazil's poor communities.
p996
tp997
a(I0
VBut where only half of the action in Midnight, the 1998 film co-directed by Salles, took viewers into the favelas (slums) of Rio De Janeiro, City Of God (which Salles co-produced) never leaves them.
p998
tp999
a(I0
VIt's entire narrative is saturated with the desperation and violence of Brazil's disenfranchised underclass.
p1000
tp1001
a(I0
VBetween 1986 and 1996, writer Paolo Lins researched the drug trade within the ironically named Cidade De Dues (City Of God), a 1960s housing project where he grew up.
p1002
tp1003
a(I0
VThe novel, and the fact it was based in, was potent raw material for a film.
p1004
tp1005
a(I0
VScreenwriter Bráulio Mantovani, director Fernando Meirelles and co-director Katia Lund have done a remarkable job of bringing this marginalised history and culture of violence to the screen.
p1006
tp1007
a(I0
VMeirelles talks of "a movie which was true to the book: filmed from the inside of the favela out."
p1008
tp1009
a(I0
VTo achieve this fidelity, the filmmakers auditioned 2,000 kids from the favelas, took 200 on to acting workshops, then improvised the scenes, free of marks, continuity control or any of the formal filmmaking strictures.
p1010
tp1011
a(I0
VAlthough the subject of the film is Cidade De Dues itself, the narrative is structured around Rocket, or Buscapé in the Portuguese (played by Luis Otavio as a kid in the 1960s, by Alexandre Rodrigues in the film's 1970s and 1980s segments).
p1012
tp1013
a(I0
VA 1960s slum kid, he observes his friends and peers opting for the gun-obsessed life of crime.
p1014
tp1015
a(I0
VAs young Li'l Dice, or Dadinho, (Douglas Silva) says, "We need to rob some rich guy's house, it's the only way out of here."
p1016
tp1017
a(I0
VRocket, however, hangs back from the endemic violence the other kids accept so readily.
p1018
tp1019
a(I0
VAs his older brother tells him shortly before being shot dead by Li'l Dice, "I'm a hood 'cos I've got no brain.
p1020
tp1021
a(I0
