VIn a world where most comedies have barely enough jokes to beef up the trailer, Monty Python And The Holy Grail stands apart.
p4325
tp4326
a(I0
VIn fact, there are so many gags they get in the way of the other good stuff.
p4327
tp4328
a(I0
VThe brilliantly-dressed sets, the painstaking attention to detail, the atmospheric Scottish landscape, the clever use of the film's one principle location (Stirling's Doune Castle) - few historical dramas are as handsome.
p4329
tp4330
a(I0
VFor all of Hazel Pethig's costume cunning and Roy Forge Smith's design wizardry, Holy Grail will probably never be recognized for its accurate recreation of the Dark Ages.
p4331
tp4332
a(I0
VFor, when all's said and done, this is a film about dismembered swordsmen, politically active peasants and knights who say "Ni!"
p4333
tp4334
a(I0
VThat such disparate elements are woven into a (fairly) coherent story is just one aspect of Grail's genius.
p4335
tp4336
a(I0
VAnother is that the film preserves the inspired formula of the Pythons' TV sketches - comprising low comedy, highbrow humour, gusto-packed musical numbers and Terry Gilliam's inimitable animation.
p4337
tp4338
a(I0
VLife Of Brian might be the (slightly) better film, but Grail is much truer to the troupe's spirit, with its tale of how Arthur (Chapman) and his men search for the cup of Christ, along the way encountering stroppy Frenchmen and an enchanter called Tim, and learning some really useful information from the man in Scene 24.
p4339
tp4340
a(I0
VThat Holy Grail is so good is all the more remarkable given how bad it could have been.
p4341
tp4342
a(I0
