VThis, the work of a single, solitary evening - presented as a lonely, intoxicating power trip - sets the stage perfectly for the film to come.The online politics of relationships, the need to not only belong but be at the top, the excitement of rage-fuelled creation and destruction, where exactly inspiration comes from and whether you can own it, the nature of friendship, the nature of competing truths, the impossibility of objectivity - these are huge ideas and The Social Network tackles them head on with a stylish wit.
p6528
